      • recordDelimiter

        public T recordDelimiter(String delimiter)
        Sets the delimiter to be the given string. The string will be converted to bytes for more efficient comparison during input parsing. The conversion will be done using the platforms default charset.
        Parameters:
        delimiter - The delimiter string.
        Returns:
        The builder itself.

      • recordDelimiter

        public T recordDelimiter(String delimiter,
                String charsetName)
        Sets the delimiter to be the given string. The string will be converted to bytes for more efficient comparison during input parsing. The conversion will be done using the charset with the given name. The charset must be available on the processing nodes, otherwise an exception will be raised at runtime.
        Parameters:
        delimiter - The delimiter string.
        charsetName - The name of the encoding character set.
        Returns:
        The builder itself.

      • field

        public T field(Class<? extends Value> type,
      int recordPosition)
        Adds a field of the record to be serialized to the output. The field at the given position will be interpreted as the type represented by the given class. The types Object.toString() method will be invoked to create a textual representation.
        Parameters:
        type - The type of the field.
        recordPosition - The position in the record.
        Returns:
        The builder itself.

      • lenient

        public T lenient(boolean lenient)
        Sets the leniency for the serializer. A lenient serializer simply skips missing fields and null fields in the record, while a non lenient one throws an exception.
        Parameters:
        lenient - True, if the serializer should be lenient, false otherwise.
        Returns:
        The builder itself.
